<div class="legal-page">
  <section class="legal-panel">
    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>Email <a href="mailto:admin@okklelab.com">admin@okklelab.com</a> for support, bug reports, privacy questions or data deletion help.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="legal-section">
    <h2>FAQ</h2>

    <h3>What is Okkle?</h3>
    <p>Okkle helps self-employed UK couriers track mileage, earnings, expenses, receipts and tax estimates for their own records.</p>

    <h3>Is Okkle tax advice?</h3>
    <p>No. Okkle is a record-keeping and estimate tool. Please confirm figures with an accountant or HMRC before filing.</p>

    <h3>Where is my data stored?</h3>
    <p>Your records are stored on your device. Okkle does not run a user account server for your mileage, earnings, expenses or receipts. If you export, back up or share files, those copies are controlled by the destination you choose.</p>

    <h3>How do I delete my data?</h3>
    <p>Open Okkle, go to Settings &gt; Data &amp; backup, then tap Delete all my data. You can also delete individual trips or records from the Records screen.</p>

    <h3>What if I need help with data deletion?</h3>
    <p>Email <a href="mailto:admin@okklelab.com">admin@okklelab.com</a> and include "Privacy" in the subject line. Because Okkle stores records on your device, you may also need to delete any exports or backups you saved separately.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="legal-panel">
    <h2>Privacy</h2>
    <p>Read the <%= link_to "Okkle Privacy Policy", privacy_path %>.</p>
  </section>
</div>
